            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Setting the value to &lt;code&gt;#&lt;/code&gt; is not inlining JavaScript. There&apos;s no JavaScript at all with that.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/695364/scott-marcus&quot; title=&quot;60,849 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Scott Marcus&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment73976182_43459971&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2017-04-17 21:41:18Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 17, 2017 at 21:41&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I&apos;m aware of that, I was referring to &lt;code&gt;onclick=&apos;getContent(event)&apos;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/693275/rob-m&quot; title=&quot;33,561 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Rob M.&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment73976198_43459971&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2017-04-17 21:41:52Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 17, 2017 at 21:41&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Yes, agreed (and I discuss that in detail in my answer). But, your reply to my comment was not about what my comment was about in the first place.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/695364/scott-marcus&quot; title=&quot;60,849 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Scott Marcus&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment73976224_43459971&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2017-04-17 21:42:43Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 17, 2017 at 21:42&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Oh no, please don&apos;t advocate &lt;code&gt;javascript:void(0)&lt;/code&gt; (it&apos;s not 1997)! Also, &lt;b&gt;if&lt;/b&gt; you were going to do this, adding &lt;code&gt;return false&lt;/code&gt; to the function wouldn&apos;t be enough. You&apos;d also need the &lt;code&gt;onclick&lt;/code&gt; attribute to look like this: &lt;code&gt;onclick=&quot;return getContent()&quot;&lt;/code&gt; and the &lt;code&gt;event&lt;/code&gt; argument wouldn&apos;t be passed to &lt;code&gt;getContent&lt;/code&gt;, it would wind up being passed to the anonymous global wrapper function that wraps it. See my answer for more details on why this is bad.&lt;/span&gt;

